Head
(
Figs. 4A–B
, 
8A–D
) small, with prominent rounded rostrum and voluminous supraocular dome surrounding large compound eye (
Figs. 4A–B
). Posterior margin of dome forming supraocular depression. Minute ocellus rounded, located near base of antenna I (
Figs. 4A–B
). Frontal head pore not revealed. Dorsal head pore round, prominent, located very close to dorsal head depression (
Fig. 4A
). Ornamentation of head is represented by polygons with tiny warts (
Figs. 8B–D
).

Pre-ephippial female (
Figs. 12A–D
).

Details of body shape and structure in pre-ephippial female similar to parthenogenetic and ephippial females. In contrast to parthenogenetic female, dorsal portion of valves in preephippial female already different from ventral portion by more fine and delicate reticulation (
Figs. 12A, D
). In contrast to ephippial female, dorsal portion of valves in preephippial female lack any traces of tubercles and processes, although position of future egg locule well visible (
Fig. 12D
).

